Review of simulation for posterior and of difference between link and sim

Import data

# Import the data
data(WaffleDivorce)
d <- WaffleDivorce
# standardize variables
d$D <- standardize( d$Divorce )
d$M <- standardize( d$Marriage )
d$A <- standardize( d$MedianAgeMarriage )
 sd( d$MedianAgeMarriage )
## [1] 1.24363
m5.1 <- quap(
    alist(
        D ~ dnorm( mu , sigma ) ,
        mu <- a + bA * A ,
        a ~ dnorm( 0 , 0.2 ) ,
        bA ~ dnorm( 0 , 0.5 ) ,
        sigma ~ dexp( 1 )
) , data = d )
set.seed(10)
prior <- extract.prior( m5.1 )
mu <- link( m5.1 , post=prior , data=list( A=c(-2,2) ) )
plot( NULL , xlim=c(-2,2) , ylim=c(-2,2) )
for ( i in 1:50 ) lines( c(-2,2) , mu[i,] , col=col.alpha("black",0.4) )


posterior predictions The procedure is exactly like the examples from the previous chapter: link mean PI plot

# compute percentile interval of mean
A_seq <- seq( from=-3 , to=3.2 , length.out=30 )
mu <- link( m5.1 , data=list(A=A_seq) )
mu.mean <- apply( mu , 2, mean )  # use apply to do vectorised calculation
mu.PI <- apply( mu , 2 , PI )
# plot it all
plot( D ~ A , data=d , col=rangi2 )
lines( A_seq , mu.mean , lwd=2 )
shade( mu.PI , A_seq )
